> would it be possible to generate a dependency tree without actually parsing the Less

Not if you use variables in imports:

```
@path: foo;
@import "@{path}/bar.less";
```

Moreover `@import` can be used inside mixins (and whatever rulesets in general):

```
.import-something(true);
.import-something(@condition) when (@condition) {
    @import "something";
}
```

So no, in general case you can't generate a dependency tree w/o actual compilation (unless you assume that only the most minimal Less subset is used, i.e. "just plain imports in the global scope").
